p2
VMusic and dance fest
p3
sVnews
p4
VAndhra Music Academy, launched by Sivananada Murthy celebrated its 9th anniversary last week at the Harihara Kala Bhavan, Secunderabad. The five-day fest began with aNadaswaramby Venugopal and party. They playedSimhavauhinias their  lead number forNenarunchinanu. Later Sivananda Murthy inaugurated the event by lighting a lamp. The festival was delayed due to the late arrival of the ministers .On day one,  S. Sashank of Chennai played the flute. He opened withBhairavi Ata Tala Varnamin two speeds. Thyagaraja&#8217;sBagayaneyyawas presented melodiously andRagam-Tanam-Pallaviwas performed in Keeravani melody.  The tanam and pallavi part was set inKahandajati triputa. This was followed by aBhajan. Ganesh Prasad on violin, Ramesh on mridangam and Nemani on ghatam lent support and displayed good team work.On the second day A. Satyanarayana and party from Tirupati presentedVadya Tarangini.  Four percussionist, a flautist, a violinist and a Nadaswaram formed his team. The Mallari inGambheeranata in khanda triputawas the highlight. Later Thodi was their main presentation forEnduku. This was followed by a vocal duet by the Malladi Brothers.  Simhendra Madhyamam was their primeragaessay,  and they playedNeedu Charanamuleof Thyagaraja. Ganesh Prasad accompanied him on the violin, P. Satish Kumar on mridangam and Nemani on the ghatam.On the third day D.Vardhani performed a vocal concert in the company of R. Dinakar on violin and P. Jayabhasker on mridangam.Kanjadalayatakshiin Kamala Manohari andSarasasamadanain Kapi Narayani were good.Kambhojiwas her main raga forMaajanaki Chettabattagawith an absorbingswarakalpana.Trichur Ramachandran of Chennai with Peri Sriramamurthy on violin, V. Kamalakara Rao on mridangam and Haribabu on ghatam, made it a memorable evening. His main raga essay was Kambhoji forEvarimaata.This was added with a delightfulswarakalpanathat spoke of his richmanodharma. On the fourth day veteran Puranam Purushothama Sastry a scholar and musicologist of Andhra performed.  He was accompanied by Kokkonda Subrahmanya Sarma on violin, Durga Kumar on mridangam and Srinivasa Gopalan on the morsing. HisHarikambhojiwas well appreciated by those present.Thodiwas his main raga and he presented that with many nuances only a veteran like him could do. Later Padmaja Reddy and party presented a dance ballet titledRadhe Srikrishnamrithan interesting piece on Lord Krishna.On the last day the the annual award ceremony took a major part of the show. Noted mridangam vidwan Yella Venkateswara Rao was conferred with the title of Sangeetha Vidyanidhi and Sobha Nayudu withNatya Vidyanidhi.After the award ceremony  a Hindustani sitar recital by world renowned sitar maestro Pandit Janardan Mitta was held in which he played two compositions. Nitin Mitta was on the tabla. He presented the raga asalap,jodandjhalain both Vilambit and Drut inteen tal. Then there was composition in Sindhu Bhairavi.In the morning there were concerts of Kalyana Vasanthand Jonnalagadda Anuradha gave a lecture demonstration on the theory and practice of Kuchipudi dance form.
